race.comment: CABLE DE VEGA (7) was quickly back on track winning comfortably at Wangaratta and then placed at Werribee over a mile. She will likely race forward, and a 2x winning wider is reunited. She looks well placed to bounce back. PROPRIETARY (2) brings narrow country defeats and the latest at Tatura stacks right up. Maps for the run of the race following a brief freshen and is a threat. CHOSEN VENTURE (5) hasn't had the best of it since his nose defeat at Swan Hill He ran a strong number that day and a bounce-back wouldn't surprise. OLNEY (1) resumed well supported at Stony Creek over a mile and didn't handle the heavy track. Has plenty in the tank and will be much more competitive in this contest. RASPUTINA (8) mixes the form but her best would give her a hope. The top Tasmanian jockey is booked.
